{#- Tier-2 #3: open-positions row expanded fragment.
    Expects: expanded (OpenPositionsExpandedVM)

    3e.8 Bundle 1 (§4.F B.AC.5): the prior V1 scope-limit "no advisories list"
    exclusion is REMOVED. Advisories are rendered inside the <td colspan="11">
    via the SAME canonical shared partial used by the dashboard list-view row
    and the trade-detail page (CLAUDE.md HTMX OOB-swap-drift gotcha — single
    canonical include target).

    Chart-display block intentionally duplicates watchlist_expanded.html.j2
    lines 33-40 (CLAUDE.md HTMX OOB-swap drift gotcha allows verbatim
    duplication when factoring would force changes outside scope; the
    watchlist expand pattern is explicitly out-of-scope per chart-access UX
    brief §2). If a future dispatch factors a shared chart_display partial,
    BOTH files must migrate together.

    Colspan must match the compact open_positions_row.html.j2 cell count
    (11 cells: Chart, Ticker, Entry date, Entry price, Shares, Current stop,
    Last, Sector, Industry, Advisory, Actions). A mismatch breaks the layout.

    HTMX-safety pre-empt list (§0.3 #7): response MUST lead with <tr> so the
    htmx.js makeFragment synthetic-table-wrap rule fires correctly for the
    `hx-target="closest tr"` + outerHTML swap convention. The new advisory
    rendering goes INSIDE the existing <tr>, not as a leading element.
-#}
<tr id="open-position-{{ expanded.trade_id }}" class="expanded">
  <td colspan="11">
    <button class="close-expanded"
            type="button"
            onclick="event.stopPropagation()"
            hx-get="/trades/open/{{ expanded.trade_id }}/row"
            hx-target="closest tr"
            hx-swap="outerHTML"
            hx-headers='{"HX-Request": "true"}'
            aria-label="Close expanded row for {{ expanded.ticker }}"
            title="Close">✕</button>
    <h3>{{ expanded.ticker }}</h3>
    {#- Phase 14 SB4 Slice 1 — inline the SB3 `position_detail` candlestick+
        risk/reward-zones SVG (read from the chart_renders cache, mirroring the
        trade-detail page) in place of the legacy static PNG.

        WP M#3 TERMINAL-else invariant: the legacy `chart_reason` /
        `chart_reason_message` come from the static-PNG chart scope, NOT the
        SVG cache. So `chart_reason is None` ("PNG available") can co-occur
        with `position_chart_svg_bytes is None` (no SVG cache row) — without a
        terminal `{% else %}` the `{% elif chart_reason_message %}` branch is
        skipped and the chart area renders BLANK. The terminal fallback below
        guarantees the operator always sees a chart or an explanatory message.

        `| safe` is applied ONLY to the matplotlib-generated SVG bytes;
        operator-/scope-derived text is auto-escaped. -#}
    {% if expanded.position_chart_svg_bytes %}
      <div class="position-detail-chart">{{ expanded.position_chart_svg_bytes.decode('utf-8') | safe }}</div>
    {% elif expanded.chart_reason_message %}
      <div class="chart-unavailable" data-chart-reason="{{ expanded.chart_reason }}">
        {{ expanded.chart_reason_message }}
      </div>
    {% else %}
      <div class="chart-unavailable" data-chart-reason="position-detail-cache-miss">
        Position chart unavailable.
      </div>
    {% endif %}
    {# Codex R2 Major #1 fix — brief §4.2 + §5 Surface 4 require the empty-
       state message to render on the expanded row too, not just on the
       trade-detail page. The shared partial intentionally emits nothing for
       an empty list; this wrapper surfaces "No advisories." in the
       expanded surface so an open trade with no triggers does not silently
       render no advisory state. #}
    {% if expanded.advisories %}
      {% with advisories = expanded.advisories %}
        {% include "partials/open_positions_advisories.html.j2" %}
      {% endwith %}
    {% else %}
      <p class="muted">No advisories.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </td>
</tr>
